50|$|Walter Kälin (born 1951 in Zurich) is a preeminent Swiss humanitarian, {{constitutional}} lawyer, {{international human}} rights lawyer, activist, and advocate. He {{is also known as}} a legal scholar and a renowned professor. He has been a leader in changing <b>Swiss</b> <b>laws</b> and international laws for humanitarian purposes and he has been published extensively on issues of human rights law, the law of internally displaced persons, refugee <b>law,</b> and <b>Swiss</b> constitutional <b>law.</b>|$|R
