50|$|The Dangerous Substances Directive (as amended) {{was one of}} {{the main}} European Union laws {{concerning}} chemical safety, until its full replacement by the new regulation CLP regulation (2008), starting in 2016. It was made under Article 100 (Art. 94 in a consolidated version) of the Treaty of Rome. By agreement, it is also applicable in the EEA, and compliance with the directive will ensure compliance with the relevant <b>Swiss</b> <b>laws.</b>|$|R
